Setting _echo_command = true
%%> \help[set]
Command: set
Description: Set a variable
Usage: \set[var=value] or \set var value
Parse Mode: Key-Value (supports [key=value] syntax)
Options:
  var - Variable name to set (required)
  value - Value to assign to the variable (required)
Examples:
  \set[name=John]
    %% Set variable 'name' to 'John' using bracket syntax
  \set name John
    %% Set variable 'name' to 'John' using space syntax
  \set[greeting="Hello World"]
    %% Set variable with quoted value containing spaces
Notes:
  Supports both bracket syntax (\set[var=value]) and space syntax (\set var value)
  Variable values can contain spaces when properly quoted
  Variables are stored in session context and persist until session ends